Sekinat Usman Ovayioza has set tongues wagging again with a new production, Idamu Adugbo. According to Ovayioza, who is also a brand ambassador and motivator, the movie was quite challenging because of the role she portrayed.   BYT accuses Burna Boy, Wizkid of hijacking title of project     Who Wants To Be a Millionaire: New sponsors speak on…     Anyiam-Osigwe blows hot over lawmakers’ take on Nollywood   Commenting on the storyline of the movie, she said: “This movie is uncommon and fascinating because I got it as an inspiration to teach the world against bad actions, drugs and to be kind and supportive to people so that one would not become an enemy to those that need one’s help. This story is didactic, full of depth in which I’m sure the world would love it. I featured a lot of actors like myself Peju ogunmola, Rotimi Salami, Aina Gold, Aisha Raji, Sola Olaibi Gaji ,Opeyemi Eniola, Madam Saje, Salimat Usman, Mimytea, Abiodun Adeoye (Afefe Oro), Taiwo and Kehinde Adebiyi and a host others. I also had my able creative director, Wasiu Adeyanju de-Genius. I love using him as my director because he is skillful and creative.” Ovayioza has featured and produced films that include Eru, Shekinah, Dangerous Wedding.   SPONSORED